{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1041,"text":"Hello, I'm Joy, a poet of code,"},{"time":4199,"text":"on a mission to stop\nan unseen force that's rising,"},{"time":9216,"text":"a force that I called \"the coded gaze,\""},{"time":12096,"text":"my term for algorithmic bias."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15429,"text":"Algorithmic bias, like human bias,\nresults in unfairness."},{"time":19753,"text":"However, algorithms, like viruses,\ncan spread bias on a massive scale"},{"time":25799,"text":"at a rapid pace."},{"time":27943,"text":"Algorithmic bias can also lead\nto exclusionary experiences"},{"time":32354,"text":"and discriminatory practices."},{"time":34506,"text":"Let me show you what I mean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36980,"text":"(Video) Joy Buolamwini: Hi, camera.\nI've got a face."},{"time":40162,"text":"Can you see my face?"},{"time":42051,"text":"No-glasses face?"},{"time":43701,"text":"You can see her face."},{"time":46237,"text":"What about my face?"},{"time":51890,"text":"I've got a mask. Can you see my mask?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56474,"text":"Joy Buolamwini: So how did this happen?"},{"time":58863,"text":"Why am I sitting in front of a computer"},{"time":62028,"text":"in a white mask,"},{"time":63476,"text":"trying to be detected by a cheap webcam?"},{"time":67150,"text":"Well, when I'm not fighting the coded gaze"},{"time":69465,"text":"as a poet of code,"},{"time":71009,"text":"I'm a graduate student\nat the MIT Media Lab,"},{"time":74305,"text":"and there I have the opportunity to work\non all sorts of whimsical projects,"},{"time":79246,"text":"including the Aspire Mirror,"},{"time":81297,"text":"a project I did so I could project\ndigital masks onto my reflection."},{"time":86455,"text":"So in the morning, if I wanted\nto feel powerful,"},{"time":88829,"text":"I could put on a lion."},{"time":90287,"text":"If I wanted to be uplifted,\nI might have a quote."},{"time":93807,"text":"So I used generic\nfacial recognition software"},{"time":96820,"text":"to build the system,"},{"time":98195,"text":"but found it was really hard to test it\nunless I wore a white mask."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104282,"text":"Unfortunately, I've run\ninto this issue before."},{"time":108652,"text":"When I was an undergraduate\nat Georgia Tech studying computer science,"},{"time":112979,"text":"I used to work on social robots,"},{"time":115058,"text":"and one of my tasks was to get a robot\nto play peek-a-boo,"},{"time":118859,"text":"a simple turn-taking game"},{"time":120566,"text":"where partners cover their face\nand then uncover it saying, \"Peek-a-boo!\""},{"time":124911,"text":"The problem is, peek-a-boo\ndoesn't really work if I can't see you,"},{"time":129364,"text":"and my robot couldn't see me."},{"time":131887,"text":"But I borrowed my roommate's face\nto get the project done,"},{"time":135861,"text":"submitted the assignment,"},{"time":137265,"text":"and figured, you know what,\nsomebody else will solve this problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141669,"text":"Not too long after,"},{"time":143696,"text":"I was in Hong Kong\nfor an entrepreneurship competition."},{"time":148339,"text":"The organizers decided\nto take participants"},{"time":151057,"text":"on a tour of local start-ups."},{"time":153453,"text":"One of the start-ups had a social robot,"},{"time":156192,"text":"and they decided to do a demo."},{"time":158128,"text":"The demo worked on everybody\nuntil it got to me,"},{"time":161132,"text":"and you can probably guess it."},{"time":163079,"text":"It couldn't detect my face."},{"time":166068,"text":"I asked the developers what was going on,"},{"time":168603,"text":"and it turned out we had used the same\ngeneric facial recognition software."},{"time":174160,"text":"Halfway around the world,"},{"time":175834,"text":"I learned that algorithmic bias\ncan travel as quickly"},{"time":179710,"text":"as it takes to download\nsome files off of the internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183745,"text":"So what's going on?\nWhy isn't my face being detected?"},{"time":186845,"text":"Well, we have to look\nat how we give machines sight."},{"time":190225,"text":"Computer vision uses\nmachine learning techniques"},{"time":193658,"text":"to do facial recognition."},{"time":195562,"text":"So how this works is, you create\na training set with examples of faces."},{"time":199483,"text":"This is a face. This is a face.\nThis is not a face."},{"time":202325,"text":"And over time, you can teach a computer\nhow to recognize other faces."},{"time":206868,"text":"However, if the training sets\naren't really that diverse,"},{"time":210881,"text":"any face that deviates too much\nfrom the established norm"},{"time":214254,"text":"will be harder to detect,"},{"time":215927,"text":"which is what was happening to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217914,"text":"But don't worry -- there's some good news."},{"time":220320,"text":"Training sets don't just\nmaterialize out of nowhere."},{"time":223115,"text":"We actually can create them."},{"time":224927,"text":"So there's an opportunity to create\nfull-spectrum training sets"},{"time":229127,"text":"that reflect a richer\nportrait of humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232975,"text":"Now you've seen in my examples"},{"time":235220,"text":"how social robots"},{"time":237012,"text":"was how I found out about exclusion\nwith algorithmic bias."},{"time":241647,"text":"But algorithmic bias can also lead\nto discriminatory practices."},{"time":247437,"text":"Across the US,"},{"time":248914,"text":"police departments are starting to use\nfacial recognition software"},{"time":253136,"text":"in their crime-fighting arsenal."},{"time":255619,"text":"Georgetown Law published a report"},{"time":257656,"text":"showing that one in two adults\nin the US -- that's 117 million people --"},{"time":264443,"text":"have their faces\nin facial recognition networks."},{"time":268001,"text":"Police departments can currently look\nat these networks unregulated,"},{"time":272577,"text":"using algorithms that have not\nbeen audited for accuracy."},{"time":276887,"text":"Yet we know facial recognition\nis not fail proof,"},{"time":280775,"text":"and labeling faces consistently\nremains a challenge."},{"time":284978,"text":"You might have seen this on Facebook."},{"time":286764,"text":"My friends and I laugh all the time\nwhen we see other people"},{"time":289776,"text":"mislabeled in our photos."},{"time":292258,"text":"But misidentifying a suspected criminal\nis no laughing matter,"},{"time":297873,"text":"nor is breaching civil liberties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300724,"text":"Machine learning is being used\nfor facial recognition,"},{"time":303953,"text":"but it's also extending beyond the realm\nof computer vision."},{"time":309266,"text":"In her book, \"Weapons\nof Math Destruction,\""},{"time":313306,"text":"data scientist Cathy O'Neil\ntalks about the rising new WMDs --"},{"time":320011,"text":"widespread, mysterious\nand destructive algorithms"},{"time":324388,"text":"that are increasingly being used\nto make decisions"},{"time":327376,"text":"that impact more aspects of our lives."},{"time":330577,"text":"So who gets hired or fired?"},{"time":332471,"text":"Do you get that loan?\nDo you get insurance?"},{"time":334607,"text":"Are you admitted into the college\nyou wanted to get into?"},{"time":338134,"text":"Do you and I pay the same price\nfor the same product"},{"time":341667,"text":"purchased on the same platform?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344133,"text":"Law enforcement is also starting\nto use machine learning"},{"time":347916,"text":"for predictive policing."},{"time":350229,"text":"Some judges use machine-generated\nrisk scores to determine"},{"time":353747,"text":"how long an individual\nis going to spend in prison."},{"time":358173,"text":"So we really have to think\nabout these decisions."},{"time":360651,"text":"Are they fair?"},{"time":361857,"text":"And we've seen that algorithmic bias"},{"time":364771,"text":"doesn't necessarily always\nlead to fair outcomes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368169,"text":"So what can we do about it?"},{"time":370157,"text":"Well, we can start thinking about\nhow we create more inclusive code"},{"time":373861,"text":"and employ inclusive coding practices."},{"time":376875,"text":"It really starts with people."},{"time":379708,"text":"So who codes matters."},{"time":381693,"text":"Are we creating full-spectrum teams\nwith diverse individuals"},{"time":385836,"text":"who can check each other's blind spots?"},{"time":388271,"text":"On the technical side,\nhow we code matters."},{"time":391840,"text":"Are we factoring in fairness\nas we're developing systems?"},{"time":395515,"text":"And finally, why we code matters."},{"time":398785,"text":"We've used tools of computational creation\nto unlock immense wealth."},{"time":403892,"text":"We now have the opportunity\nto unlock even greater equality"},{"time":408363,"text":"if we make social change a priority"},{"time":411317,"text":"and not an afterthought."},{"time":414008,"text":"And so these are the three tenets\nthat will make up the \"incoding\" movement."},{"time":418554,"text":"Who codes matters,"},{"time":420230,"text":"how we code matters"},{"time":421797,"text":"and why we code matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423844,"text":"So to go towards incoding,\nwe can start thinking about"},{"time":426967,"text":"building platforms that can identify bias"},{"time":430155,"text":"by collecting people's experiences\nlike the ones I shared,"},{"time":433257,"text":"but also auditing existing software."},{"time":436351,"text":"We can also start to create\nmore inclusive training sets."},{"time":440140,"text":"Imagine a \"Selfies for Inclusion\" campaign"},{"time":442967,"text":"where you and I can help\ndevelopers test and create"},{"time":446646,"text":"more inclusive training sets."},{"time":449302,"text":"And we can also start thinking\nmore conscientiously"},{"time":452154,"text":"about the social impact\nof the technology that we're developing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457569,"text":"To get the incoding movement started,"},{"time":459986,"text":"I've launched the Algorithmic\nJustice League,"},{"time":462857,"text":"where anyone who cares about fairness\ncan help fight the coded gaze."},{"time":468753,"text":"On codedgaze.com, you can report bias,"},{"time":472073,"text":"request audits, become a tester"},{"time":474542,"text":"and join the ongoing conversation,"},{"time":477337,"text":"#codedgaze."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480742,"text":"So I invite you to join me"},{"time":483253,"text":"in creating a world where technology\nworks for all of us,"},{"time":486996,"text":"not just some of us,"},{"time":488917,"text":"a world where we value inclusion\nand center social change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493529,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494728,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":500873,"text":"But I have one question:"},{"time":503751,"text":"Will you join me in the fight?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":505834,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":507143,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}